### ENVIRONMENTAL ARTIFACT (session native4, check 8): a 'click [data-testid=btn-lock-toggle]' invocation timed out at the CLI level and left the agent-browser daemon in a click-retry loop — a capture-phase listener on the button counted thousands of ongoing DOM click events (samples: 7904 -> 10766 -> 12808, still growing at ~130-180 clicks/sec) with NO further CLI commands issued. This made the lock readouts oscillate and explains the inconsistent post-flip snapshot recorded above (lockDisabled 'false' with cells 0). Tool artifact, not the app: page 'errors' remained empty throughout, and the app's own counter select-lock-events stayed 0 the whole time. Recovery: page reload to detach the loop target; check 8 is rerun cleanly below.

